metadata.name: Artifice #75
metadata.description:
This series is is about playful obfuscation.

The fxtext article linked on the main profect goes more in-depth into what is meant by that, as well as the events that led to this collection.

5640 bytes of Vanilla JS with no libraries. Palettes make up a third of the code.

In live mode:
‘S’ : save as png (3000 × 3600)
’V’ : save as svg (without grain)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=p’ : paper grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 9000 ×10600 (Chrome only, and may take a moment)

For example, if you wanted paper grain in high resolution, append “&g=p&h=t” to the url in live mode.

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save a png with those settings applied.

metadata.name: Commune #26
metadata.description:
A minimalist composition with a nod towards architecture.

2932 bytes of Vanilla JS.

For more info, see article linked below: Me, Commune, Etc.

In live mode:
’S’ : save as svg (without grain)
‘P’ : save as png (3780x2673)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=w’ : wood grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 7560 × 5346 (Chrome only)

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save the png with those settings applied.

metadata.name: Pobbles #130
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

• The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
• See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
• Alternative titles considered include Peggles™, Plops™, Blobbies™, Floofs™, Flintstones™, Lardies™, Plumps™, Fats™ and Wet-Ones™. 
• The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
• The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
• They work well with toddlers.

🖨️ Collectors minting at the first auction tier receive a hand-crafted riso print of their pobble. Color variation between the file and the print will apply. 🖨️

metadata.name: Slumbers #200
metadata.description:
Generative abstract artwork that explores forms, shapes, coloring and brushwork.

Options:

- press 'f' to turn off paper-like texture (recommended for print on hi-quality paper)
- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Colors and textures might differ slightly on some devices due to the heavy use of low alpha blending. Calibrated and tested on Firefox 107.0 & Chrome 107.0.5304.107 on Win10 x64 Intel machine.

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, November, 2022.

metadata.name: Nanopanorama #36
metadata.description:
Distorted noise with weird textures and funky shapes rendered using my rayhatcher algorithm.

4671 characters of pure Javascript, no libraries.

Some options can be changed via the URL:

&lw=.25 : The linewidth in millimetres.
&d=.4 : Line density (multiplier to linewidth).
&h=235 : Page height in millimetres. The aspect ratio is 16:9, for a width of 420mm, suitable for A3 plotting.
&bg=1 : Set to 0 to remove background rectangle (recommended for plotting).

When plotting, it is recommended to use a path reordering / optimizing tool such as axicli or vpype to greatly reduce the plotting time.
